'''Luka Sučić''' ({{IPA|hr|lûːka sûtʃitɕ}};<ref>{{cite web|url=http://hjp.znanje.hr/index.php?show=search_by_id&id=e15vWBE%3D|title=Lȗka|quote=Lȗka|website=Hrvatski jezični portal|accessdate=30 November 2020|language=hr}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=|first=|date=|title=sẉd<sup>1</sup>|url=http://hjp.znanje.hr/index.php?show=search_by_id&id=d1pjWxI%3D&keyword=sud|archive-url=|archive-date=|accessdate=30 November 2020|website=Hrvatski jezični portal|language=hr|quote=Sȕčić}}</ref> born 8 September 2002) is a professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[midfielder]] for [[La Liga]] club [[Real Sociedad]]. Born in Austria, he plays for the [[Croatia national football team|Croatia national team]].

==Club career==
On 15 July 2020, Sučić signed a new contract with [[FC Red Bull Salzburg|Red Bull Salzburg]], until the summer of 2024.<ref>{{cite web |title=Sučić Gets New Contract |url=https://www.redbullsalzburg.at/en/fc-red-bull-salzburg/news/saison_2019_20/sucic-gets-new-contract.html |website=redbullsalzburg.at |publisher=FC Red Bull Salzburg |accessdate=15 July 2020 |date=15 July 2020}}</ref>

He made his [[2020–21 Austrian Football Bundesliga|Bundesliga]] debut for Salzburg on 13 September 2020 in a game against [[Wolfsberger AC|Wolfsberg]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Soccerway|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2020/09/13/austria/bundesliga/wolfsberger-athletik-club/fc-red-bull-salzburg/3341874/|title=Wolfsberger v Red Bull game report|date=13 September 2020|access-date=2026-06-02}}</ref> On 25 November 2020, he made his [[2020–21 UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] debut, replacing [[Dominik Szoboszlai]] in 71st minute and providing [[Rasmus Kristensen]] with a pre-[[Assist (association football)|assist]] for [[Mërgim Berisha]]'s goal, as Salzburg lost 3–1 to [[FC Bayern Munich|Bayern Munich]].<ref>{{Cite web|last=|first=|date=26 November 2020|title=Naš novi bik iz Salzburgova inkubatora: Luka Sučić ostavio je dobar dojam protiv Bayerna|url=https://telesport.telegram.hr/na-prvu/nas-novi-bik-iz-salzburgova-inkubatora-luka-sucic-ostavio-je-dobar-dojam-protiv-bayerna/|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=30 November 2020|website=Telesport|language=hr}}</ref> On 10 February 2021, Sučić scored his debut Bundesliga goal in a 3–1 victory over [[FK Austria Wien|Austria Wien]], coming off the bench to replace Berisha.

[[File:FC Red Bull Salzburg gegen Wolfsberger AC (2022-02-20) 32.jpg|thumb|left|180px|Sučić with [[FC Red Bull Salzburg|Red Bull Salzburg]] in 2022]]
By the beginning of the [[2021–22 FC Red Bull Salzburg season|2021–22 season]], Sučić already established himself in Salzburg's squad, most notably scoring an impressive goal against [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]] in a friendly 2–1 victory on 4 August 2021.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|last=Jurišić|first=Bernard|date=28 August 2021|title=Novi val dijaspore|url=https://telesport.telegram.hr/kolumne/juris/novi-val-dijaspore/|access-date=28 August 2021|website=Telesport|language=hr}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vecernji.hr/sport/salzburg-srusio-barcelonu-sucic-zabio-fenomenalan-gol-1513272|title=Salzburg srušio Barcelonu, Sučić zabio fenomenalan gol|author=[[Croatian News Agency|HINA]]|website=Večernji list|date=4 August 2021|access-date=28 August 2021|language=hr}}</ref> On 14 September, he scored his first [[2021–22 UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] goal in a 1–1 draw with [[Sevilla FC|Sevilla]].<ref>{{Cite web|date=14 September 2021|title=Kakav početak Lige prvaka: Hrvati strijelci na čudnoj utakmici na kojoj su dosuđena četiri penala!|url=https://gol.dnevnik.hr/clanak/rubrika/nogomet/liga-prvaka-ivan-rakitic-i-luka-sucic-strijelci-na-utakmici-sevilla-red-bull-salzburg---666682.html|access-date=14 September 2021|website=Gol.hr|language=hr}}</ref>

On 1 August 2024, he signed a 5-year contract with [[La Liga]] club [[Real Sociedad]] for a €10m fee plus a 10% sell-on clause.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.realsociedad.eus/es/noticias/detalle/sucic-nuevo-jugador-txuri-urdin |title=Sučić, nuevo jugador txuri urdin |publisher=Real Sociedad |language=es |date=2 August 2024 |access-date=2026-06-02}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Ituarte |first=Sean |url=https://www.mundodeportivo.com/futbol/real-sociedad/20240802/1002291624/obra-olabe-medular.html |title=Otra obra de Olabe para la medular |publisher=Mundo Deportivo |language=es |date=2 August 2024 |access-date=2026-06-02}}</ref> Later that year, on 6 October, he scored his first La Liga goal in a 1–1 draw against [[Atlético Madrid]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Buxton |first=Richard |url=https://onefootball.com/en/news/atletico-de-madrid-frustrated-by-late-draw-at-real-sociedad-40136962 |title=Atlético de Madrid frustrated by late draw at Real Sociedad |publisher=OneFootball |date=6 October 2024 |access-date=2026-06-02}}</ref> On 20 February 2025, he netted a brace in a 5–2 win against [[FC Midtjylland|Midtjylland]] during the [[2024–25 UEFA Europa League knockout phase|Europa League knockout play-offs]] second leg, helping his team advance to the round of 16.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/match/_/gameId/732211/fc-midtjylland-real-sociedad |title=Real Sociedad 5–2 FC Midtjylland |publisher=ESPN |date=20 February 2025 |access-date=2026-06-02}}</ref>

==International career==
Eligible for [[Austria national football team|Austria]], [[Bosnia and Herzegovina national football team|Bosnia and Herzegovina]] and [[Croatia national football team|Croatia]], Sučić explicitly opted for Croatia, despite interest from the [[Austrian Football Association]].<ref name="24sata1">{{cite web|url=https://www.24sata.hr/sport/sucic-nedavno-su-me-pozvali-i-u-austriju-ali-meni-je-oduvijek-zelja-bila-zaigrati-za-hrvatsku-751311|title=Sučić: Nedavno su me pozvali i u Austriju, ali meni je oduvijek želja bila zaigrati za Hrvatsku!|last1=Tironi|first1=Hrvoje|website=[[24sata (Croatia)|24sata]]|language=hr|date=23 March 2021|accessdate=24 March 2021}}</ref> On 9 March 2021, he was named in [[Igor Bišćan]]'s [[2021 UEFA European Under-21 Championship squads#Croatia|23-man squad]] for the group stage of [[2021 UEFA European Under-21 Championship|UEFA Under-21 Euro 2021]];<ref>{{Cite web|last=Kajtazi Roth|first=Anita|date=9 March 2021|title=Bišćan objavio popis igrača za U-21 Euro: Na njemu najviše igrača Dinama i neka nova imena|url=https://gol.dnevnik.hr/clanak/rukomet-2021/biscan-objavio-popis-igraca-za-u-21-euro-na-njemu-najvise-igraca-dinama-i-neka-nova-imena---643144.html|access-date=24 March 2021|website=[[Gol.hr]]|language=hr}}</ref> however, he was ruled out on 21 March due to an injury and replaced by [[Matej Vuk]].<ref>{{Cite web|last=[[Croatian News Agency|HINA]]|date=21 March 2021|title=Bišćan umjesto ozlijeđenog Sučića pozvao Mateja Vuka|url=https://www.24sata.hr/sport/biscan-umjesto-ozlijedenog-sucica-pozvao-mateja-vuka-752086|access-date=24 March 2021|website=[[24sata (Croatia)|24sata]]|language=hr}}</ref> On 17 May, he was named in Bišćan's [[2021 UEFA European Under-21 Championship squads#Croatia 2|23-man squad]] for the knockout stage of the tournament;<ref>{{Cite web|last=[[Croatian News Agency|HINA]]|date=17 May 2021|title=Bišćan objavio popis za U-21 Euro: Pozvao i sjajnog mladog hajdukovca|url=https://gol.dnevnik.hr/clanak/hrvatska-reprezentacija/biscan-objavio-popis-za-u-21-euro-pozvao-i-sjajnog-mladog-hajdukovca---652149.html|access-date=25 May 2021|website=[[Gol.hr]]|language=hr}}</ref> however, the same occurred and he was replaced by [[Neven Đurasek]] on 25 May.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Olivari|first=Davorin|date=25 May 2021|title='Baš šteta, cijela Hrvatska je konačno htjela vidjeti tog dečka!' Bišćan najavio i sina legende Vatrenih|url=https://sportske.jutarnji.hr/sn/nogomet/reprezentacija/bas-steta-cijela-hrvatska-je-konacno-htjela-vidjeti-tog-decka-biscan-najavio-i-sina-legende-vatrenih-15075786|access-date=25 May 2021|website=[[Sportske novosti]]|language=hr-hr}}</ref> 

During [[2023 UEFA European Under-21 Championship qualification Group A|UEFA Under-21 Euro 2023 qualifiers]] in September and October 2021, Sučić scored three goals and assisted once in three games, prompting [[Zlatko Dalić]] to call him up to the senior team on 9 October, two days ahead of a [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification – UEFA Group H|World Cup qualifier]] against [[Slovakia national football team|Slovakia]], due to [[Mateo Kovačić]]'s suspension.<ref>{{Cite web|date=9 October 2021|title=Luka Sučić pozvan u reprezentaciju za utakmicu protiv Slovačke|url=https://www.index.hr/clanak.aspx?id=2309663|access-date=9 October 2021|website=[[Index.hr]]|language=hr}}</ref> He made his senior debut in the said qualifier, which ended as a 2–2 draw.<ref>{{Cite web|date=11 October 2021|title=On će remi sa Slovacima pamtiti cijeli život: "Fenomenalan osjećaj, sanjao sam o ovome"|url=https://gol.dnevnik.hr/clanak/hrvatska-reprezentacija/luka-sucic-odusevljen-poslije-debitantskog-nastupa-za-hrvatsku-reprezentaciju---679320.html|access-date=12 October 2021|website=[[Gol.hr]]|language=hr}}</ref>

On 9 November 2022, Sučić was named in Dalić's [[2022 FIFA World Cup squads#Croatia|26-man squad]] for the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.index.hr/sport/clanak/dalic-objavio-popis-za-svjetsko-prvenstvo-u-kataru/2410337.aspx |title=Dalić objavio popis za Svjetsko prvenstvo u Kataru |website=[[Index.hr]] |access-date=2022-12-18 |date=2022-11-09 |language=hr}}</ref> where he remained an unused substitute as Croatia finished third.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.index.hr/mobile/sport/clanak/pet-igraca-hrvatske-nije-dobilo-ni-minutu-na-svjetskom-prvenstvu/2421887.aspx |title=Pet igrača Hrvatske nije dobilo ni minutu na Svjetskom prvenstvu |website=[[Index.hr]] |date=2022-12-17 |access-date=2022-12-18 |language=hr}}</ref> Due to the recovery process from knee surgery he underwent in March 2023,<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-03-10 |title=Sportske novosti - Najteža ozljeda u karijeri i operacija ugrožavaju veliki ljetni transfer hrvatskog reprezentativca? |url=https://www.jutarnji.hr/sportske/kosarka/kosarka-reprezentacija/najteza-ozljeda-u-karijeri-i-operacija-ugrozavaju-veliki-ljetni-transfer-hrvatskog-reprezentativca-15314060 |access-date=2026-06-02 |website=www.jutarnji.hr |language=hr-hr}}</ref> Sučić was omitted from [[2023 UEFA Nations League Finals squads#Croatia|Croatia's 23-man squad]] for the [[2023 UEFA Nations League Finals]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Zlatko Dalić objavio konačan popis za Ligu nacija: Otpao je mladi napadač |url=https://gol.dnevnik.hr/clanak/rubrika/hrvatska-reprezentacija/zlatko-dalic-objavio-konacan-popis-za-ligu-nacija---785426.html |access-date=2026-06-02 |website=Gol.hr |language=hr}}</ref> 

On 20 May 2024, Sučić was named in Dalić's preliminary 35-man squad for [[UEFA Euro 2024]];<ref>{{cite web| title = Zlatko Dalić objavio popis igrača za Europsko prvenstvo u Njemačkoj| website = HNS.team| publisher = [[Hrvatski nogometni savez]]| date = 2024-05-20| access-date = 2025-06-16| url = https://hns.team/vijesti/27847/zlatko-dalic-objavio-popis-igraca-za-europsko-prvenstvo-u-njemackoj/| language = hr}}</ref> on 7 June 2024, he made it to the [[UEFA Euro 2024 squads#Croatia|final 26]].<ref>{{cite web| title = Prijavljena konačna lista igrača za Europsko prvenstvo u Njemačkoj| website = HNS.team| publisher = [[Hrvatski nogometni savez]]| date = 2024-06-07| access-date = 2025-06-16| url = https://hns.team/vijesti/27960/prijavljena-konacna-lista-igraca-za-europsko-prvenstvo-u-njemackoj/| language = hr}}</ref> At the tournament, he played in all three matches,<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-10-31 |title=Evropa bruji o fudbaleru porijeklom iz Bosne i Hercegovine: "To se viđa jednom u životu" |url=https://sportsport.ba/fudbal/luka-sucic-gol-oktobra-real-sociedad-eurogol/485171 |access-date=2026-06-02 |website=SPORTSPORT |language=hr}}</ref> as Croatia finished their campaign already in the [[UEFA Euro 2024 Group B|group stage]].

In May 2025, Sučić was called up for Croatia's [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification – UEFA Group L|2026 FIFA World Cup qualifiers]] against [[Gibraltar national football team|Gibraltar]] and [[Czech Republic national football team|Czechia]], played on 6 June and 9 June, respectively. Ahead of the Czechia game, Sučić left the national team's camp to attend his sister's wedding in [[Gornji Vakuf-Uskoplje|Uskoplje]], allegedly angering Dalić. Dalić refrained from commenting on the issue in public.<ref>{{cite web| title = Luka Sučić neće igrati protiv Češke. Dalić: Razlozi su privatni| website = [[Index.hr]]| date = 2025-06-08| access-date = 2025-06-16| url = https://www.index.hr/sport/clanak/luka-sucic-nece-igrati-protiv-ceske-dalic-razlozi-su-privatni/2678729.aspx| language = hr}}<br>{{Cite news |last=Demopoulos |first=Alaina |date=2026-06-02 |title=ww88 |url=https://ww88aw.com |access-date=2026-06-02 |language=en-GB}}<br>{{cite web| title = Afera Sučić: Hoće li ga Dalić i dalje zvati? Čeka li ga 'edukativni proces' ili će proći bolje od Ćaleta-Cara?| website = [[Sportske novosti]]| date = 2025-06-12| access-date = 2025-06-16| url = https://sportske.jutarnji.hr/sn/nogomet/nogomet-medjunarodni/afera-sucic-hoce-li-ga-dalic-i-dalje-zvati-ceka-li-ga-edukativni-proces-ili-ce-proci-bolje-od-caleta-cara-15593660| language = hr| last = Antolić| first = Dražen}}<br>{{Cite web|url=https://budica.info/sestra-ili-repka-dalic-je-otpisao-luku-sucica/|title=SESTRA ILI REPKA Dalić je otpisao Luku Sučića!|date=2025-06-14|access-date=2025-06-16|website=Budica.info|last=Begović|first=Damir|language=hr}}</ref> 

When Dalić announced the list of players for the September matches against the [[Faroe Islands national football team|Faroe Islands]] and [[Montenegro national football team|Montenegro]], it was apparent that Sučić was not called-up.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-08-18 |title=Dalić potvrdio ekskluzivu SN-a! Sučić na 'hlađenju', nakon dugo vremena nema igrača Dinama, Petkoviću pretpoziv |url=https://sportske.jutarnji.hr/sn/nogomet/reprezentacija/dalic-potvrdio-ekskluzivu-sn-a-sucic-na-hladenju-nakon-dugo-vremena-nema-igraca-dinama-petkovicu-pretpoziv-15613934 |access-date=2025-08-18 |website=[[Sportske novosti]] |language=hr-hr}}</ref> Dalić denied that Sučić was "either written off, or punished, or chased away" at a press conference ahead of the Faroe Islands game.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://gol.dnevnik.hr/clanak/rubrika/hrvatska-reprezentacija/zlatko-dalic-o-luki-sucicu-ja-nisam-ovdje-da-kaznjavam-nego-da-stitim-obitelj---932170.html|title=Zlatko Dalić o Luki Sučiću: "Ja nisam ovdje da kažnjavam nego da štitim obitelj"|date=2025-09-01|access-date=2025-09-01|website=[[Gol.hr]]|language=hr}}</ref> However, Sučić did receive an additional call-up before the October matches against Czechia and Gibraltar.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://sportske.jutarnji.hr/sn/nogomet/sp2026/dalic-pozvao-novu-dvojicu-igraca-luka-sucic-ponovno-je-u-kadru-nakon-afere-vjencanje-15629718 |website=[[Sportske novosti]] |title=Dalić pozvao novu dvojicu igrača! Luka Sučić ponovno je u kadru nakon 'afere vjenčanje' |first=Ante |last=Buškulić |date=2025-10-06 |access-date=2025-12-18 |language=hr}}</ref> On 12 October, in a 3–0 victory against the latter opponent, he scored his first goal for the national team.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.index.hr/mobile/sport/clanak/luka-sucic-zabio-je-prvi-gol-za-reprezentaciju-pogledajte-ga/2719313.aspx|title=Luka Sučić zabio je prvi gol za reprezentaciju. Pogledajte ga |website=[[Index.hr]] |date=2025-10-12|access-date=2025-12-18 |language=hr}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Sučić was born in [[Linz]] to [[Bosnian Croat]] parents Željko and Branislava from [[Bugojno]] who fled from the [[Bosnian War]]. Despite being born in Linz, Sučić does not hold [[Austrian nationality law|Austrian citizenship]]. He declared himself a fan of [[HNK Hajduk Split|Hajduk Split]] and [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]]; however, he named [[Luka Modrić]], a legend of those clubs' respective rivals [[GNK Dinamo Zagreb|Dinamo Zagreb]] and [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]], as his footballing [[role model]].<ref name="24sata1"/><ref>{{Cite web|last=Topić|first=Mihovil|date=6 October 2021|title=Veliki dečko|url=https://telesport.telegram.hr/price/veliki-decko/|access-date=9 October 2021|website=Telesport|language=hr}}</ref> His cousin [[Petar Sučić]] is also a footballer.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://sportske.jutarnji.hr/sn/nogomet/hnl/klubovi/dinamo/mladi-talent-postaje-sve-vaznija-karika-dinama-prvijenac-protiv-hajduka-bio-bi-mi-najdrazi-gol-karijere-15403226|title=Sportske novosti - Mladi talent postaje sve važnija karika Dinama: 'Prvijenac protiv Hajduka bio bi mi najdraži gol karijere'|date=10 December 2023|website=sportske.jutarnji.hr|access-date=2026-06-02}}</ref>

